                Nstocks is a web application for the Stock market. It receives the data for the stocks from the Alpha
                Vantage
                and visualizes them with charts. Anyone who uses the web application has the capability to monitor
                current high, low, close, previous close and open values. You can also register to the application and
                therefore, as a user you can follow your favorite stocks in order for them to be organized in your
                Profile. Another advantage of being a user at Nstocks is that you can set upper and lower bounds for a
                specific stock and if its value decreases or increases, the server will send you an notification email.
                The back-end is built with Nodejs, express and other packages from npm , while the front-end is built
                with Bootstrap, EJS, CSS and Javascript. The server makes API calls and then sends the data to the
                client, which visualizes them with charts for the timeline of: 1 Day, 2 Days, 1 Month, 5 Months, 1 Year,
                5 Years and Max years. Both of the server and the client communicate with AJAX. The web application is
                online with the usage of Heroku and Github.

